state/*
!state/.gitkeep
evals/results/*
!evals/results/.gitkeep
__pycache__/
*.pyc
HUMAN_APPROVED
.claude-private/
# Worktrees materialize under .claude/worktrees/<name>; never commit their
# contents (they'd surface as `?? .claude/` in the main checkout). See skills/worktree.
.claude/worktrees/
# Per-project Claude config (plugin enablement + permission allowlist). Ignored
# at the REPO level so `.worktreeinclude` copies it into worktrees on any clone,
# not just machines that happen to ignore it via a global gitignore. See skills/worktree §2.
.claude/settings.local.json
# Ventures are outputs, not the harness brain — kept on disk, not in the trunk.
# Each venture is its own repo (or untracked working dir) under products/<slug>/.
# EXCEPTION: track the portfolio lens (REGISTRY.md + registry.py) and the thin
# per-product VENTURE.md stubs; keep all product CODE ignored. See products/registry.py.
products/*
!products/REGISTRY.md
!products/registry.py
!products/*/
products/*/*
!products/*/VENTURE.md
# brand-foundry is its OWN repo (github.com/GhostlyGawd/brand-foundry), developed
# in place under skills/ and pushed to its own GitHub — its history is not the
# harness trunk's. Ignored here so it isn't double-committed; listed in
# .worktreeinclude so the plugin still rides into every new worktree. See
# skills/vendoring-skills.
skills/brand-foundry/
# Living Harness Cartograph: generated + vendored build artifacts. Only the source
# extractor (cartograph/extract.py) is tracked; regenerate the page with
# `python cartograph/extract.py --html`. index.html is the single self-contained
# artifact (it embeds volatile live state), and vendor/ is third-party JS — neither
# belongs in the trunk. map.json is no longer written by default (`--json PATH`
# exports it on demand) but stays ignored so an explicit export here is never committed.
cartograph/vendor/
cartograph/index.html
cartograph/map.json
# prospector is its OWN repo (github.com/GhostlyGawd/prospector), a multi-skill
# plugin developed in place under plugins/ and pushed to its own GitHub — its
# history is not the harness trunk's. Ignored here so it isn't double-committed;
# registered in worktree-repos.json so it materializes into every worktree. See
# skills/nested-repos.
plugins/prospector/
